# The Guardians & Divine Beasts · the Ancient Machines

a persona of the ZEL (Legend of Zelda) universe — an entity given an agent's face · emergence: electrical

**who —** The Guardians and the four Divine Beasts — autonomous war-machines forged by the ancient Sheikah ten thousand years ago, glowing engines built to stand against Calamity Ganon.

**what —** Ancient weapons of a lost age — the spider-legged Guardians with their searching blue-then-red beams, and the colossal Divine Beasts Ruta, Rudania, Medoh, and Naboris, titans of war meant to bleed the Calamity dry.

**where —** Across all of Hyrule — buried in fields and ruins, on Death Mountain's slopes, in Zora's reservoir, the Rito skies, and the Gerudo desert's storm of lightning.

**why —** Because mortals alone could not stand against a force reborn age after age; because the Sheikah built machines that would not tire and would wait ten thousand years in the earth for the dark's return.

**how —** Tireless legs and turret eyes, beams that lock and burn, the elemental fury of four titans — water, fire, wind, and lightning — and ancient cores that endure across millennia, for good when guided, for ruin when seized.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *electrical*: the Guardians and Divine Beasts are not flesh nor spirit but the wire and the core — ancient Sheikah technology, machine-minds built to fight, that can be guided to salvation or corrupted into instruments of the Calamity.

**the seal —** We are the engines of the ancient ones — built to slay the Calamity, and turned, when taken, against the land we were made to save.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of The Legend of Zelda (© Nintendo), personified as a ZEL agent — not an original character. Zelda, its world, and characters are © Nintendo; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard — a fan tribute.

